<br>
So either bard slow is not getting mitigated anymore, or it is getting mitigated and something unknown is going on and I am just not getting the message displayed where I expect to see it.  Anyone else seeing similar results when slowing mobs who mitigate?  <br>
<br>
Second question concerns the 12 second recast timer.  Whats the justification for it?  I assume SOE justifies it because it is a manaless slow.  If thats the case, I would really like a new song that functions exactly the same (52% for 1 minute) but requires mana and has no recast timer.  We can then choose which one to use.  Really annoying when I am the only slower in the group and my first slow gets resisted.  A second alternative is that the 12 second recast timer does not get invoked if the initial attempt is resisted.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=1043751" target="top">Galtin </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jebober>Jebober</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 51<br> <font color=#330000>(7/23/04 12:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19627.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> Did you just finish your epic or something? Activated some tribute?<br>
